
1. ESP waking immediately after sleep

Problem

GPIO stayed active causing instant wakeups. while testing using gpio 10 and 11 and connecting them with ground 
everything work as intended,
but when i used the same firmware on the real water meter. the magnet stopped moving just below one of the gpio 
causing instant wakeups

Solution

Removed flawed stuck-mode wake logic.
Switched to transition-based behavior. before sleeping i checked whether the gpio is high or low. if its high i 
configured the sleep to wake on low and vice verca.
Corrected EXT1 polarity handling.
3. GPIO stuck HIGH forever

Problem

Static HIGH on hall sensor caused repeated wake behavior.

Solution

Ignore static state.
Only count transitions/pulses.
Sleep normally if no activity
.
