You need to replace these with a connection table or an array of per-connection contexts.

2) Scan logic that cancels after the first meter

In gap_event() under BLE_GAP_EVENT_EXT_DISC, you currently do this:

ble_gap_disc_cancel();

That means the reader stops scanning as soon as it finds one meter, then connects to only that one. For multiple meters, this has to change.

3) Connect callback

In BLE_GAP_EVENT_CONNECT, you assign:

connected   = true;
auth_done   = false;
conn_handle = event->connect.conn_handle;

That is another single-peer assumption. For multiple meters, this must become “create a new session entry for this conn_handle.”

4) Auth receive path

In BLE_GAP_EVENT_NOTIFY_RX, you are checking the notify data against one global auth_done and one global text_handle. That is also single-connection only. Each connection needs its own auth state and its own handles.

5) Commands and reads

These functions all use the one global connection:

send_cmd(...)
ble_gattc_read(conn_handle, ...)
do_auth()

So if you want multiple meters, these must take a connection context or connection handle parameter instead of using the globals.





