meter_storage_init() is masking EEPROM/storage failures. It calls meter_storage_load(), logs a warning if it fails, but
still returns ESP_OK and marks storage initialized. That means the rest of the firmware 
can keep running on defaults even when EEPROM is unreadable or commit fails, which will
hide real field problems.


/* =============================================================================
 * main.c  —  Water Meter Firmware
 *
 * FIXES vs previous version
 * ──────────────────────────
 * FIX-1  LoRa fires every 120 s even while BLE is connected.
 *        wm_request_lora_window_if_needed() + wm_run_lora_window() are now
 *        called inside WM_STATE_BLE_CONNECTED.  LoRa TX runs inline (no state
 *        transition) so the BLE session is never interrupted.
 *
 * FIX-2  No pulse undercount while BLE is connected.
 *        last_count is now updated unconditionally in wm_handle_pulses(),
 *        even when time is invalid or the save path is skipped.  This means
 *        delta can never silently accumulate across ticks.
 *
 * FIX-3  Duplicate meter_storage_init() on cold boot removed.
 *        The bare call at the top of wm_boot_once() that swallowed its own
 *        error has been removed; only the ESP_ERROR_CHECK version remains.
 *
 * FIX-4  auth_start_us declared as RTC_DATA_ATTR in this file.
 *        Previously it was used here but only defined in meter_helper.c,
 *        meaning it never survived deep sleep.
 *
 * FIX-5  Hardware poll (tamper + pulses) now excluded during
 *        WM_STATE_PREPARE_SLEEP and WM_STATE_LORA_WINDOW to prevent
 *        concurrent EEPROM writes.
 *
 * FIX-6  Sleep request suppressed while BLE is actively connected.
 *        wm_request_sleep_if_needed() now returns early when
 *        nimble_adv_is_connected() is true.
 *
 * FIX-7  LORA_WINDOW state now restores correct previous state (RUN or
 *        BLE_ADV) instead of always jumping to RUN.
 * ============================================================================= */
